# 05-audit-trail.md — durable session log

Each row of the table below is one session. The row is written when a session
closes or hits a meaningful checkpoint. Format is intentionally rigid so that
`bin/qwen-coldstart.ps1` can parse it without ambiguity.

## Format

`| S-id | STATUS | agent. one-line summary. |`

- **S-id**: `S-YYYYMMDD-<short-tag>` (e.g. `S-20260507-vault-fullscope`).
- **STATUS**: one of `OPEN`, `CLOSED`, `BLOCKED`, `SUPERSEDED`, `LOCKED`.
- **agent**: short hex codename (e.g. `agent-a3f7`) so multiple agents on
  multiple machines stay distinguishable in shared logs.
- **summary**: one paragraph. Telegraphese is fine. Preserve exact paths,
  version numbers, hex IDs, file names. End with what was UNTESTED.

Full detail per session lives in `REVIVAL-S<id>-*.md` on disk and (if you have
a brain) under brain tag `<S-id>`.

## Compaction

Once `05-audit-trail.md` exceeds ~30k tokens of loaded context, compress
verbose rows into `archive/closed-sessions-archive.md` and replace with
one-line stubs. `bin/latest-revival.ps1` is the inverse — it expands a single
revival doc back into prose on demand.

